</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/125449978-hagen-seah"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_100x100-c7bfe730633c9983e27caaa66a8e244a.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/125449978-hagen-seah">Hagen Seah</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">i would say this is fine, though if you are pretty resistant to reading the titular essay which involves didion&apos;s encounters with drugs in san francis<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">i would say this is fine, though if you are pretty resistant to reading the titular essay which involves didion's encounters with drugs in san francisco, i would suggest avoiding that particular essay on its own, which doesn't affect your understanding of the other essays in any way. the rest is pretty standard and shouldn't be much of an issue.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
